Does your child love Cat in the Hat by Dr Seuss? If so, this fun party theme is ideal for both boys and girls. Here’s how to throw an epic Cat in the Hat party – and best of all, you can do so on a budget! Ideas for a Cat in the Hat party Choose a classic Cat in the Hat style piñata. . The hats on each place setting also have secret hollow centres to fill with goodies for each child. If you have time, you can make them yourself or buy them from Piñata’s Galore (info@pinatasgalore.co.za). Make your child’s birthday party fun from the get-go with this Cat in the Hat party invitation. Download your template here. Blue candy floss atop vanilla cupcakes replicates Thing 1 and Thing 2’s crazy hairdos, and the kids will love it. Here’s how to make it: Ingredients Method Ingredients for icing with blue candy floss Method Two round cakes make a hat cake, and the red, blue, and white roll-out icing provides the detail. Or you can bake a one-layer round cake and have a picture from the book printed on rice paper to lay on top. Coconut ice made red and white instead of the traditional pink and white brings through the colours in the cat’s hat. Click here for a recipe. Small details like these hat and alphabet biscuits complement the theme perfectly. Here’s how to make them: Ingredients: Method: